Description.
WORKER (n=3) (
Fig. 62A–C
): HL (1.16–1.24); HW (1.06–1.18); ML (0.64–0.72); SL (0.80–0.86); MOD (0.28–0.31); PNW (0.72–0.82); WL (1.34–1.48); PSL (0.18–0.20); PL (0.62–0.68); PW (0.28–0.34); PPL (0.34–0.40); PPW (0.36–0.44); GL (1.22–1.42); TL (5.32–5.78); CI (91.38–97.45); SI (71.30–75.47); OI (26.08– 26.41). Large-sized. Shiny integument. Black body, brownish mandibles, trochanter and tarsus. Mostly thin and unbranched setae, midsized to short, suberect to subdecumbent; thick branched setae flattened in its final half, with several branches, mainly in the postpetiole and gaster (
Fig. 80J
).
